node.text:
Cannafam, My friend Anthony of @40tonsbrand came by to let us know that @40tonsbrand is hosting a Canna Get a 2nd Chance Career Fair this Thursday, in Hawthorne, CA!! Some of the awesome services provided will be:
🌱 Expungement services by @m4mmunited
🌱 Resume & Linkedin Coaches
🌱 Employers looking for candidates (plant-touching & non-plant touching careers)
🌱 Professional Headshots
🌱 Chance at winning a scholarship to Oaksterdam University
🌱 A panel of cannabis professionals on career tips + much more!
Register on Eventbrite & make sure you follow @40TonsBrand for more information! 💗

node.title: 40 Tons Industry Career Fair this Thursday (9/2/21)

node.text: On May the 4th 1970, the #KentState Massacre occurred and cannabis ended up as a scapegoat, which led to some pretty awful legislation that still exists today 😔 Full video can be found on @herb’s Facebook page! I’m there every Tuesday at 12p PST!

node.text:
I decided to interview my twin brother @cannabistim12! His second cannabis interview ever! 

We went down memory lane and talked about his business endeavors Legal dispensary, @goodkarmacannabisco + Hookah & Consumption Lounge @hubblybubblyokc + A Positive News Podcast @thepositivetruthpodcast + A Smoke Shop @trifectaokc 🔥Tim is killin it 👏🏽 #proudsister

node.text:
🚨LEGALIZE IT EVERYWHERE🚨
America is making huge gains on the drug war, but did you know legalization in other parts of the world benefits us and the planet? 🌎Let’s help push India’s cannabis/medicinal herb reform efforts! 🇮🇳 Here’s how to do it:
✨First, follow @hempvati!
✨Second, go to the link in my bio! Under “Cannabis Reform,” you will find the submission link for opinions and suggestions on cannabis, psilocybin and other herbs to India’s government.
✨Share and tell a friend or family member to help, too!

I believe we can affect change globally! Will you help?

node.text:
A new study reports 15% of remote employees worked from home while using cannabis. ⁠
⁠
Of that 15%, 52.9% reported decreased stress, 51.1% reported increased creativity, 42.6% reported increased productivity, and 17.8% wanted to smoke with their boss.⁠
⁠
Can you relate to any of these statistics? Let me know in the comments!⁠
⁠
[source: American Marijuana]⁠
⁠
📷: @redheadedstranger_420

node.text:
The cannabis plant is an ally; Get the best out of her energy and properties by paying attention to how different strains affect you. No one person is the same!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Cannabis journals are a great way to track your experiences with different strains. You can use the journal to help you discover and remember your preferences, experiences and usage. There's nothing worse than swearing you won't smoke a strain again, forgetting, and buying it the next time you're at the dispensary.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Are any of you fans of keeping a cannabis journal or log? Why or why not? Sound off in the comments!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷: @sheweedcbd

node.text:
Cannabis & Mindfulness: Cannabis effects can prove extra beneficial when meditating. Your body enters a more relaxed state - something that is very important when getting in the zone. Your breathing deepens - slowing, regulating, focusing on breath becomes easier. Your awareness is heightened - if you had other stimulus this might seem distracting, but when meditating it increases the chances of your mind wandering into itself and tapping in to that sweet spot.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Do you incorporate cannabis into your meditation practices? 🌟✨⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷: @nat_geode

node.text:
This post is for my cannabis newbies.. Are you collecting your kief? [The powdery substance made of trichomes and resin glands that is attached to and removed from the cannabis flower] You can find it collected nicely inside of your grinder. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Don't get rid of your kief - it's pretty much cannabis gold if taken care of! You can sprinkle this into or onto your joints and bowls, decarb it to cook with it, or even make hash and shatter concentrates. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
How do you use your kief? ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷: @sugarhousesocialclub

node.text:
ICYMI: Last month it was announced that staff at New York airport checkpoints are no longer looking for, seizing, issuing tickets for possession, or making weed-related arrests at airports across the state.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
But don't get it twisted, while they may not be actively searching for it, if TSA finds cannabis in your belongings, they are still technically required to contact law enforcement. So play it safe out there while the war on drugs lives on.

node.text:
We've all heard at least once from prohibitionists that cannabis causes cognitive decline.. But did you know the facts actually say otherwise?⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Studies have been done on different controlled age groups, and no evidence has been found to support the idea that cannabis consumption leads to a decline in our neurocognitive ability or IQ scores.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
So next time your canna-hating aunt has something to say, let her know the facts! ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
[Source: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷: @48nrth
